So here's the deal on "Zorrita": It's boring. Surrender Cinema definitely has worse films in circulation, because at least this one shows a fair amount of full frontal (though not enough considering how good-looking the female cast is), but the plot is so thin and the sex scenes so blase that it's difficult to watch this without falling asleep. It had a female director and maybe that's the reason.

Clearly, Surrender Cinema was running out of ideas by this point.  Still, they could have put a little more effort into it.  Shauna O'Brien is the ONLY reason to watch this one, but let's face it, that's a good reason!  Honestly, for O'Brien fans.

I was disappointed with this one!  I mean, why cast all of these beautiful young women in a Zorro-like parody, but then show nothing but incredibly lame guy/girl scenes.  Only ONCE does beautiful dark-haired Zorrita (Shauna O'Brien) climb into bed with another woman, and that one was all watered-down and bland.  Where are the creative directors nowadays?  Where are the dominant/submissive lesbian scenes that we all used to enjoy so much?  Certainly not here.  Yes, if you want to see some female nudity, watch this one, but be prepared for a lot of uninteresting male nudity, as I seriously believe that the writer/director of this one may have been more interested in looking at guys.
The Main Thing Is Shauna O Brien Wasn't Bad Looking From My View Anyway!
